# unsupported(forReason:)

**Type Method**

Creates an object whose resolution requires the user to confirm the task list before continuing.

## Declaration

```swift
class func unsupported(forReason reason: INDeleteTasksTaskListUnsupportedReason) -> Self
```

## Parameters

- **reason**: The reason that deletion isn’t supported.

## Return Value

A new [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INDeleteTasksTaskListResolutionResult] object.

## Discussion

Use this method to create a resolution result object when your app doesn’t support the intent parameter for the specified reason.

## Creating a Resolution Result

- **init(taskListResolutionResult:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves successfully deleting a task from a task list.
- **INDeleteTasksTaskListUnsupportedReason**: Constants that indicate the reason an app can’t support the delete task request.
